{
  "title": "How to disable throttling for Exchange Online",
  "slug": "how-to-disable-throttling-for-exchange-online",
  "categorySlug": "data-sources",
  "html": "<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell \" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-1 dnd-section kb-article-row-0-padding\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell dnd-column\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-2 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-2\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-3 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h1 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">How to disable throttling for Exchange Online</h1>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-4 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h2 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">When Office365 throttles a user, it slows down the GDPR scanner - This is how to avoid that.</h2>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-5 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_richtext_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_richtext_field\"><div>\n<p><strong>What is throttling?</strong></p>\n<p>Throttling is a security mechanism that keeps a server healthy and responsive. It is called \"throttling\" because it limits the workload coming through the server by regulating network traffic and minimizing bandwidth congestion. As a result, you may experience slow Internet and performance speeds, which in turn can impact the speed of your backup or restore.</p>\n<p>Throttling is a general condition that all Microsoft Office 365 applications have to deal with and it is not something that can be affected or changed through configuration or regular troubleshooting.</p>\n<p>Microsoft offers only a limited amount of bandwidth to each of their Office 365 or OneDrive customers and applications installed by those customers cannot go beyond those limits. Allocation of bandwidth is based on the number of licensed users on the platform.</p>\n<p><br><strong>Disable EWS throttling in Exchange Online</strong></p>\n<p><strong><br></strong><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">1. Log in to the Office 365 admin page with your Global admin credentials. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">2. Open the Admin app.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" style=\"width: 200px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png.png\" width=\"200\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=100&amp;name=image-png.png 100w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png.png 200w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=300&amp;name=image-png.png 300w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=400&amp;name=image-png.png 400w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=500&amp;name=image-png.png 500w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png.png?width=600&amp;name=image-png.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">3. In the left navigation pane, select Support and then New service requests.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" style=\"width: 200px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png-1.png\" width=\"200\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=100&amp;name=image-png-1.png 100w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png-1.png 200w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=300&amp;name=image-png-1.png 300w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=400&amp;name=image-png-1.png 400w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=500&amp;name=image-png-1.png 500w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-1.png?width=600&amp;name=image-png-1.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">4. In the search field, search for throttling. Select <strong>Increase EWS Throttling Policy</strong> from the list and press Enter.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><img class=\"hs-image-align-none\" style=\"width: 200px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png-2.png\" width=\"200\" srcset=\"https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=100&amp;name=image-png-2.png 100w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=200&amp;name=image-png-2.png 200w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=300&amp;name=image-png-2.png 300w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=400&amp;name=image-png-2.png 400w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=500&amp;name=image-png-2.png 500w, https://support.dataandmore.com/hs-fs/hubfs/image-png-2.png?width=600&amp;name=image-png-2.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"></span></p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>5. Select Run Tests. Diagnostic tests will run.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">6. Select the duration in days. The options are 30 days, 60 days, and 90 days. Check the checkbox to acknowledge the change and then select Update Settings. -</span><strong>&gt; choose 90 days.</strong></p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>7. You will see a message showing that the update to Exchange Web Services (EWS) throttling policy has been successfully initiated. The update will complete within 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>8. After 15 minutes run the test again to check if the changes are applied. This time you will see that Exchange Web Services (EWS) is currently not throttled.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div>\n</div>",
  "sourceUrl": "https://support.dataandmore.com/en/knowledge/how-to-disable-throttling-for-exchange-online"
}